Jeanette Chabalala, News24Two miners trapped in a mine have died. (ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The second man who was trapped in a mine on Stanley Road in Primrose, Germiston has died, paramedics said on Friday.The man was brought to the surface and declared dead around 00:00 on Friday, ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall told News24.The owner and one employee of the mine had descended more than 75m into the mine to check on water levels around 15:00 on Thursday.One man was declared dead at 18:00 while the other one remained trapped.Siddall said both had run out of oxygen. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.